    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="911"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/12–744</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Department of State refers to an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> dated
                    November 28, 1944, Reference: 152/221/44, from the British Embassy concerning
                    the interrogation of a captured member of the S.S. Deathshead Division who was
                    taken into custody in France.</p>
                <p>The American Government is of the opinion that until information received from
                    the prisoner has been evaluated, no interrogation should be made except by
                    British and American officers under the direction of the Supreme Headquarters,
                    Allied Expeditionary Forces. The prisoner was captured by the First American
                    Army and it is believed to be in the best interests of the United States not to
                    permit interrogation of him at this time by Polish or Soviet officers.</p>
                <p>A message has been dispatched to Supreme Headquarters, Allied Expeditionary
                    Forces, requesting interrogation of this prisoner within the theater in
                    accordance with the above decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-18">December 18,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
